President Donald Trump called the U.S. men’s national ice hockey team on Thursday morning ahead of... President Donald Trump called the U.S. men’s national ice hockey team on Thursday morning ahead of its 4 Nations Face-Off final against Canada. USA Hockey posted a photo of the team listening to Trump over the phone’s speaker in the locker room. Ahead of the call, Trump posted on Truth Social that he was calling the players “to spur them on towards victory tonight against Canada, which with FAR LOWER TAXES AND MUCH STRONGER SECURITY, will someday, maybe soon, become our cherished, and very important, Fifty First State.”
